posts.body: That happened to me when I got a new certificate identity. I was using a self-signed one for 08chan but switched to a ZeroID cert and I had to re-blacklist boards.

posts.subject: /pol/ not showing up?
posts.body: On the 08chan front page, /pol/ is not listed. I didn't blacklist it. Sometimes it shows up under the "New posts" list at the bottom. I can navigate directly to the /pol/ main page and everything shows up, but it just won't show up on the 08chan front page. Any ideas?

>>4ac916f8-0f2a-465c-99bc-a3cada493f49
No. I even set it to show all boards on a single page and /pol/ still doesn't show up.

>>adef7355-2f41-4169-a2e0-1dfc564d91a7
Well, that was it. I don't remember muting /pol/, but I guess I accidentally did at some point. Thanks you, kind anons.

>>ff47a76e-9e2c-4f75-9605-071f9d0cc834
Ah, I see. Well, I unmuted and restarted ZeroNet. It's showing up again now. Thanks.
